==Subgroups==
{{Main|Girls' Generation-TTS}}
On April 19, 2012, SM Entertainment officially announced the creation of the Girls<U+2019> Generation subunit, Girls<U+2019> Generation<U+2013>TaeTiSeo, composed of Taeyeon, Tiffany, and Seohyun. The subunit's first mini-album ''[[Twinkle (EP)|Twinkle]]'' was released on April 29, 2012. According to a statement made by SM Entertainment, "This subunit will aim to grab the attention of fans with all aspects of music, performance, and fashion styles."{{citation needed|date=November 2013}}

==Artistry==

===Musical style===
{{Listen
| filename = Gee-SNSD.ogg
| title    = <nowiki>"Gee"</nowiki>
| description = 2009's Gee, a predominately [[teen pop]] song with influences of [[dance pop]] which incorporates the use of a memorable hook.<ref name="interview1" />
| format   = [[Ogg]]
}}

During the beginning of their career, the group's music was predominantly [[bubblegum pop]] and [[teen pop]]. Singles such as "[[Gee (Girls' Generation song)|Gee]]" and "[[Oh! (Girls' Generation song)|Oh!]]" utilize the teen pop and bubblegum pop genres while incorporating [[dance pop]]<ref name="interview1">Kim, Hyeon-woo and Jee, Hyeong-joon. [http://news.joins.com/article/3446478.html?ctg=15 <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300><U+AC00> <U+B3CC><U+C544><U+C654><U+B2E4>! <U+201C>9<U+AC1C><U+C6D4><U+B9CC><U+C5D0> <U+CEF4><U+BC31>, <U+BAB8> <U+ADFC><U+C9C8><U+ADFC><U+C9C8><U+D588><U+B2E4><U+201D>(<U+C778><U+D130><U+BDF0><U+2460>) (''Girls' Generation Has Returned! "Comeback After 9 Months, We're Excited" (Interview Part 1)'')]. ''[[Joongang Ilbo|Joins.com]]/Newsen''. January 6, 2009. Retrieved January 5, 2009.</ref><ref name="KenizeOh">{{ko icon}} Yang Ji-won. [http://news.joins.com/article/931/3984931.html?ctg=15 <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+C2A4><U+D0A4><U+B2C8><U+C9C4><U+2192><U+B9C8><U+B9B0><U+B8E9> <U+C774><U+C5B4> <U+C774><U+BC88><U+C5D4> <U+2018><U+C2A4><U+D3EC><U+D2F0><U+2019> (''Girls' Generation, from Skinny Jeans to Marine Look, Now "Sporty"'')]. ''[[JoongAng Ilbo]]''. January 26, 2010. Retrieved January 26, 2010.</ref> In 2009 the group transitioned to [[electropop]] sound with the release of "[[Tell Me Your Wish (Genie) (song)|Tell me Your Wish (Genie)]]".<ref name=sportsseoul>[http://www.sportsseoul.com/news2/entertain/hotentertain/2009/0714/20090714101040100000000_7209885622.html <U+C5F0><U+C608> <U+2013> <U+AE30><U+C0AC><U+B0B4><U+C6A9> <U+2013> "<U+C9C0><U+AE08><U+C774> <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300><U+C77C><U+AE4C>?<U+2026><U+C544><U+C9C1>, <U+C6B0><U+B9AC><U+C2DC><U+B300><U+B294> <U+BA40><U+C5C8><U+B2E4>" (<U+C778><U+D130><U+BDF0>)]. Sportsseoul.com (June 13, 2010). Retrieved on October 30, 2011.</ref> The group continued this sound when debuting in Japan with ''[[Girls' Generation (2011 album)|Girls' Generation]]'', using a more [[electropop]]<ref name=CrazyLondon>{{cite web|title=London is going K-Pop crazy|url=http://www.musicasia.net/london-is-going-k-pop-crazy/|publisher=MusicAsia|accessdate=November 30, 2011}}</ref> influenced sound.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://seoulbeats.com/2012/06/side-b-shoujo-jidai-brings-the-fans-out/|title=Side B: Shoujo Jidai Brings the Fans Out|date=June 16, 2012|accessdate=October 2, 2012|publisher=seoulbeats.com|author=Subi}}</ref> They would carry this sound onto their second Japanese album with songs like "[[Paparazzi (Girls' Generation song)|Paparazzi]]" and "[[Flower Power (song)|Flower Power]]", the latter was noted for its use of a flowing base and prominent synths.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2012/10/02/kiji/K20121002004238120.html|title=<U+5C11><U+5973><U+6642><U+4EE3><U+3000><U+30B7><U+30F3><U+30B0><U+30EB><U+FF11><U+4F4D><U+FF01><U+FF11><U+FF10><U+5E74><U+FF19><U+6708><U+306E><U+65E5><U+672C><U+30C7><U+30D3><U+30E5><U+30FC><U+4EE5><U+6765><U+521D>|date=October 2, 2012|accessdate=November 26, 2012|publisher=sponichi.co.jp}}</ref> The group works extensively on Korean releases with producers [[Yoo Young-jin]] and [[Kenzie (songwriter)|Kenzie]].<ref name="KenizeOh" /><ref>{{cite news|last=Kang|first=Myoung-seok|title=Record producer Yoo Young-jin <U+2013> Part 2|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010061113544954123|accessdate=May 20, 2012|newspaper=10 Asia|date=June 11, 2010}}</ref> Lyrically, the group explores [[girl power|female empowerment]], evident in songs like "[[Hoot (song)|Hoot]]" and "[[The Boys (Girls' Generation song)|The Boys]]."<ref name="hitquarters.com"/><ref name="ryan">{{cite web |url=http://ryanseacrest.com/2011/10/18/k-pop-group-girls-generation-release-english-version-of-the-boys-video/ |title=K-Pop Group <U+2018>Girls<U+2019> Generation<U+2019> Release English Version of <U+2018>The Boys<U+2019> |accessdate=October 23, 2011 |publisher=Ryan Seacrest |author=Jen Erenza |date=October 2011}}</ref> The first member to participate in the creation of the group's work was [[Kwon Yuri|Yuri]], who co-wrote the R&B-inspired song "Mistake" (<U+B0B4> <U+C798><U+BABB><U+C774><U+C8E0>) from the group's third EP ''[[Hoot (EP)|Hoot]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1010250031|title=<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> <U+C720><U+B9AC> <U+CCAB> <U+C791><U+C0AC><U+ACE1> <U+C120><U+BCF4><U+C778><U+B2E4>..<U+C815><U+D1B5> R&B <U+ACF5><U+B7B5>|date=October 25, 2010|accessdate=December 11, 2012|publisher=osen.t.co.kr}}</ref> The group extended more control with [[Tiffany Hwang|Tiffany]] and [[Sooyoung]] co-writing "The Boys," and "How Great Is Your Love" on the group's third Korean album, ''[[The Boys (Girls' Generation album)|The Boys]]'', respectively.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=106&oid=003&aid=0004142436 |language=Korean |title=<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+ACBD><U+AD6C> <U+B418><U+C0B4><U+B9AC><U+B2E4><U+2026><U+C18C><U+B144><U+B4E4><U+C774><U+C5EC> <U+C57C><U+B9DD> <U+AC00><U+C838><U+B77C> :: <U+B124><U+C774><U+BC84> <U+B274><U+C2A4> |deadurl=no |accessdate=February 12, 2013}}</ref> The group's fourth album, [[I Got a Boy]], combines many different musical elements such as [[New wave music|80s new wave]], [[electronic dance music]], and [[Contemporary R&B|modern R&B]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|title=Girls' Generation, 'I Got A Boy': Track-By-Track Review |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/1481602/girls-generation-i-got-a-boy-track-by-track-review|publisher=Billboard|accessdate=January 4, 2013}}</ref> while their single "[[I Got a Boy (song)|I Got a Boy]]" is an example of electronic dance song that mixes pop, retro, and urban genres.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://girlsgeneration.smtown.com/ |title=Girls Generation Official Website |deadurl=no |accessdate=February 12, 2013}}</ref> "Romantic St.", a track in their fourth studio album I Got a Boy, was described by '' [[Naver|Naver Music]]''  as belonging to the [[jazz]] and [[Swing music|swing]] music genres.<ref name="naver">{{cite web|url=http://music.naver.com/album/index.nhn?albumId=359839|title=I Got A Boy - 4th album by Girls' Generation|date=January 1, 2013|accessdate=November 4, 2013|language=[[Korean language|Korean]]|publisher=[[Naver|Naver Music]]}}</ref> [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] described "Flower Power" as a harmony-heavy, robo-pop jam, and "I Got a Boy" as a grab-bag of genres jumping from drum 'n' bass to clunky electro-pop. "Galaxy Supernova" is backed by a pulsing synth, and the b-side "Do the Catwalk," contains a super-catchy, whistle hook.<ref>{{cite news|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|title=Girls' Generation Releases 'Galaxy Supernova' in Japan|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/5695513/girls-generation-releases-galaxy-supernova-in-japan|accessdate=November 29, 2013|newspaper=Billboard|date=September 17, 2013}}</ref> Girls' Generation Japanese single, [[Love & Girls]] was noted to have a peppy piece of electro-pop with referee whistles acting as the hook.<ref>{{cite news|title=Girls' Generation Releases 'LOVE&GIRLS' in Japan; New Albums Ahead|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/1562863/girls-generation-releases-lovegirls-in-japan-new-albums-ahead|accessdate=November 29, 2013|newspaper=Billboard|date=June 18, 2013}}</ref>

===Imagery===
The group's image has been a major role in their rise in popularity. In the early years of their career, the group wore relatively no makeup and dressed more conservatively. The song "Kissing You" had the girls use lollipops as a prop during performances.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mediaus.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=14626 |language=Korean |title=<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300><U+B294> <U+C5B4><U+B5BB><U+AC8C> <U+C2DC><U+B300><U+C758> <U+CD1D><U+C544><U+AC00> <U+B418><U+C5C8><U+B098> <U+2013> <U+BBF8><U+B514><U+C5B4><U+C2A4> |deadurl=no |accessdate=February 12, 2013}}</ref> During promotions for their 2009 single "Gee", the group dressed in jeans and plain-white shirts, highlighting the "purity" of the group and the song.<ref>[http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=106&oid=111&aid=0000137503 <U+BCC4> "<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+C74C><U+C545> <U+B118><U+C5B4><U+C120> <U+C544><U+C774><U+CF58>!"]<U+300A><U+C870><U+C774><U+B274><U+C2A4><U+300B>,2009<U+B144> 3<U+C6D4> 9<U+C77C></ref> When promoting the "Oh!" single in January 2010, the group used a cheerleader concept.<ref>{{ko icon}} Choi Jong-pyeon. [http://news.sbs.co.kr/section_news/news_read.jsp?news_id=N1000702214 <U+C7A5><U+B3D9><U+AC74>-<U+ACE0><U+C18C><U+C601> '5<U+C6D4> <U+ACB0><U+D63C><U+C124>'<U+2026><U+C544><U+C774><U+D2F0> <U+B3D9><U+BC18> <U+BC29><U+BB38> <U+CD94><U+C9C4> (''Jang Dong-geun<U+2013>Go So-young "Wedding in May"...IT Company Interview Propulsion'')]. ''[[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS News]]''. January 26, 2010. Retrieved January 26, 2010.</ref> The group left behind their 'pure' image, opting for a more mature image during the promotions for "Tell Me Your Wish (Genie)". The concept was based off marines, with members dressing in short-shorts highlighting their legs.<ref name="Genie release" /> The choreography was designed around their legs and became popular in Korea "Jegi-kicking dance" ({{lang|ko|<U+C81C><U+AE30><U+CC28><U+AE30> <U+CDA4>}}) and the "Leg-beauty dance" ({{lang|ko|<U+AC01><U+C120><U+BBF8> <U+CDA4>}}).<ref>[http://www.asiae.co.kr/uhtml/read.jsp?idxno=2009062620283612085 '<U+CEF4><U+BC31>' <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, '<U+AD70><U+BB34>' <U+D37C><U+D3EC><U+BA3C><U+C2A4> <U+C77C><U+B2E8> '<U+D569><U+ACA9><U+C810>']. asiae.co.kr. 2009.06.26</ref> For 2010's "[[Hoot (song)|Hoot]]", the group's image was based on [[Bond Girl]]s.<ref name="concepts">{{cite web|url=http://article.joinsmsn.com/news/article/article.asp?total_id=6819071|title=<U+C18C><U+B140><U+D2F0> <U+BC97><U+C744><U+B798> <U+2026> <U+BCF5><U+ACE0><U+D48D> <U+C78A><U+C5B4><U+C918>|publisher=article.joinsmsn.com|date=December 5, 2011|accessdate=November 26, 2012}}</ref> Earlier that year, whilst gearing up for promotion for "[[Run Devil Run (Girls' Generation song)|Run Devil Run]]", the group was noted for using a much darker, sexy image, nicknamed "Black SoShi".<ref>[http://star.mt.co.kr/view/stview.php?no=2010031711450033387&outlink=2&SVEC '<U+BE14><U+B799><U+C18C><U+C2DC>' <U+C724><U+C544><U+00B7><U+D2F0><U+D30C><U+B2C8><U+AC00> <U+B9C8><U+C9C0><U+B9C9><U+C5D0> <U+ACF5><U+AC1C><U+B41C> <U+C774><U+C720>]<U+300A><U+BA38><U+B2C8><U+D22C><U+B370><U+C774><U+300B>, 2010<U+B144> 3<U+C6D4> 17<U+C77C></ref> In 2011, the group returned to Korea with "[[The Boys (Girls' Generation song)|The Boys]]", which used a "heroine" image, with members choosing their own outfits, emphasizing each of the members' own tastes.<ref name="concepts" /> When creating choreography, the group works with [[Rino Nakasone Razalan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rino Nakasone Official Twitter Page|url=http://twitter.com/#!/RinOkinawa/status/62774234774110208|publisher=Microblog at Twitter.com|accessdate=July 3, 2011}}</ref> During the promotions of ''[[I Got a Boy]]'', the group opted to the use of flat shoes instead of their trademark heels in order to perform the choreography correctly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=106&oid=109&aid=0002461705|title=<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+D558><U+C774><U+D790> <U+BC97><U+B294><U+B2E4>... <U+D37C><U+D3EC><U+BA3C><U+C2A4> <U+B09C><U+C774><U+B3C4><U+2191>|date=December 27, 2012|accessdate=December 27, 2012|publisher=news.naver.com|language=Korean}}</ref>

John Seabrook from ''[[The New Yorker]]'' described Girls' Generation as "a group of preppy-looking young women in skinny trousers. When they wear hot pants, it<U+2019>s to display the gams, not the glutes." <ref>[http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2012/10/08/121008fa_fact_seabrook Cultural Technology and the Making of K-Pop : The New Yorker<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> ''[[New York Magazine]]'' stated that the music itself is not the decisive factor in the popularity of K-pop as a whole, and Girls' Generation in particular. But rather the that the public likes the groups based on its members' looks and their personality, radiating a "humility" and friendliness to each and one of the fans.<ref name="nymagazine20121010">{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/thecut/2012/10/grown-men-moved-by-south-korean-girl-groups.html|title=Grown Men Creepily Moved by South Korean Girl Groups|publisher=[[New York Magazine]]|date=October 1, 2012|accessdate=October 2, 2012}}</ref>
Kevin Perry from the British music publication ''[[NME]]'' wrote: "Girls<U+2019> Generation also have a massive nine members, which is indicative of the way the efficient K-pop machine can favour choreographed style over individual personalities."<ref>[http://www.nme.com/blog/index.php?blog=1&title=korea_prospects_a_beginner_s_guide_to_k_&more=1&c=1&tb=1&pb=1 Beyond 'Gangnam Style' <U+2013> A Beginner<U+2019>s Guide To K-Pop <U+2013> NME Blogs <U+2013> NME.COM <U+2013> The world's fastest music news service, music videos, interviews, photos and more<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

==Impact and legacy==
{{Main|Korean Wave|List of awards and nominations received by Girls' Generation}}
Following their debut in 2007, Girls' Generation has become a prominent figure in both South Korean culture and music, with music critics noting the group as being a representative figure of [[South Korean culture]].<ref>[http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=106&oid=111&aid=0000137503 <U+BCC4> "<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+C74C><U+C545> <U+B118><U+C5B4><U+C120> <U+C544><U+C774><U+CF58>!"]<U+300A><U+C870><U+C774><U+B274><U+C2A4><U+300B>,2009<U+B144> 3<U+C6D4> 9<U+C77C>]{{ko}}</ref> The group is credited as playing a major role in the [[Korean Wave|Hallyu Movement]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.donga.com/3/all/20101116/32629541/1|language=korean|title=<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>-<U+CE74><U+B77C><U+AC00> <U+65E5> <U+2018><U+C81C>2<U+C758> <U+D55C><U+B958><U+2019> <U+C774><U+B04C><U+C5B4>|author=<U+B0A8><U+C6D0><U+C0C1>|accessdate=November 26, 2012|date=November 16, 2011|publisher=news.donga.com}}</ref> and have been compared to fellow K-Pop singer [[Seo Taiji]] due to their contributions to Korean culture.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.donga.com/3/all/20100128/25752219/1|title=[O2/<U+CEE4><U+BC84><U+C2A4><U+D1A0><U+B9AC>]<U+C11C><U+D0DC><U+C9C0><U+C640> <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>|date=April 26, 2010|accessdate=November 26, 2012|author=<U+C815><U+D638><U+C7AC>|publisher=news.donga.com|language=Korean}}</ref> Their immense popularity has led the group to earn the titles "The Nation's Singers" (Korean: <U+AD6D><U+BBFC><U+AC00><U+C218>) and "The Nation's Girl Group"<ref name="2010<U+B144> <U+C62C><U+D574><U+C758> 10<U+B300> <U+AC00><U+C218><U+C640> <U+AC00><U+C694>"/> Following the disbandment of the original Korean idol girl groups [[S.E.S. (band)|S.E.S.]] and [[Fin.K.L]] in 2002, the Korean music industry experienced an influx of male idol groups such as [[TVXQ!]] and [[Super Junior]], however upon the group's debut with songs such as "[[Into the New World (song)|Into the New World]]" and "[[Kissing You (Girls' Generation song)|Kissing You]]", they were credited for shifting focus back to female groups.<ref>{{cite web|title=<U+B274><U+C2A4> <U+C778><U+C6A9>|url=http://www.mediaus.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=14626|language=Korean}}</ref> In 2011, the group was chosen by [[Tyler Br<U+00FB>l<U+00E9>]] as the seventh most recognizable Korean culture figure, being the only musical and non-object act to make the list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://article.joinsmsn.com/news/article/article.asp?total_id=4929531&cloc=olink|title=<U+BE48><U+B300><U+B5A1>, <U+BA85><U+D488> <U+D328><U+C2A4><U+D2B8><U+D478><U+B4DC> <U+B420> <U+C218> <U+C788><U+B2E4>|date=January 15, 2011|accessdate=November 26, 2012|publisher=article.joinsmsn.com|author=Lee Eun Joo|language=Korean}}</ref> The group's fashion has been described as "chic" and "mature", becoming immensely popular among young women across Asia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20110213n03742|title=[TD<U+D3EC><U+D1A0>] <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> <U+C720><U+B9AC> '<U+C62C> <U+BE14><U+B799><U+C73C><U+B85C> <U+ACF5><U+D56D><U+D328><U+C158> <U+C885><U+ACB0>!'|publisher=news.nate.com|date=February 13, 2011|accessdate=November 26, 2012}}</ref> With many dubbing the group as "fashion icons".<ref name="<U+D0C1><U+C7AC><U+D6C8>"><U+D0C1><U+C7AC><U+D6C8><U+C758> <U+C2A4><U+D0C0><U+C77C> <U+2013> <U+C2A4><U+D0C0>Q10' <U+300A>E!TV <U+300B>,SBS,2010<U+B144> 12<U+C6D4> 1<U+C77C> <U+BC29><U+C1A1>.</ref> In Japanese textbooks, the group serves as the main feature in the K-Pop section of the book.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kr.ibtimes.com/article/news/20110816/6300913.htm|title=<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> <U+65E5> <U+AD50><U+ACFC><U+C11C> <U+B4F1><U+C7A5>, <U+C804> <U+C138><U+ACC4><U+AC00> <U+C8FC><U+BAA9> "<U+C644><U+BCBD><U+D55C> <U+D37C><U+D3EC><U+BA3C><U+C2A4><U+2026><U+B9E4><U+B8CC><U+B3FC>"|date=August 16, 2011|accessdate=November 26, 2012|publisher=kr.ibtimes.com|author=Angela}}</ref>
[[File:SNSDfans.jpg|thumb|left|Girls' Generation has consistently gained fans over the years.]]

The group gained significant popularity at the start of 2009 with the release of "[[Gee (Girls' Generation song)|Gee]]", the single was named 'Single of the Decade' and broke the record on KBS' ''Music Bank'' for the most consecutive wins in a row.<ref name="news.jkn.co.kr"/> The single is regarded as one of the first K-Pop songs to gain international attention, students at [[Harvard University]] in the United States highlighted the song as part of their study on Korean culture, with some performing the song's famous choreography.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kr.news.yahoo.com/service/news/shellview.htm?linkid=16&articleid=20090321094731920b6&newssetid=83|date=March 21, 2009|accessdate=November 26, 2012|publisher=kr.news.yahoo.com|title=[<U+B2E8><U+B3C5>]<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>,<U+D558><U+BC84><U+B4DC><U+5927><U+B85C><U+C2A4><U+CFE8> <U+D559><U+C0DD><U+B4E4><U+C5D0> '<U+C9C0>' <U+AC00><U+B974><U+CE5C><U+B2E4>|language=Korean}}</ref> Their popularity has also translated into economic success. They are regarded as the most sought-out advertiser in South Korea.<ref name="bntnews.hankyung.com">{{ko icon}}[http://bntnews.hankyung.com/apps/news?popup=0&nid=04&c1=04&c2=04&c3=00&nkey=200909280929513&mode=sub_view CF <U+D038><U+C73C><U+B85C> <U+B4F1><U+ADF9><U+D55C> <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+AD11><U+ACE0><U+ACC4><U+B3C4> <U+C811><U+C218> ('CF Queens SNSD takes over the Advertisement World')]</ref> Marketers named the group as the model with the most influence over consumers, attributing the group's positive attention from the public to their vocals, looks, and fashion sense.<ref name="acrofan.com">{{ko icon}}[http://www.acrofan.com/ko-kr/life/news/?mode=view&cate=02&seq=23479&wd=20101222&ucode=00000007&page=1 <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+AC00><U+C694><U+ACC4>-<U+AD11><U+ACE0><U+ACC4> <U+B3D9><U+C2DC> <U+C11D><U+AD8C> (Girls Generation Takes Over Music Scene, and Now CF Scene)]</ref> In 2011 the group generated $57&nbsp;million from Japanese releases.<ref name="http"/> And a further USD$88.56 million in South Korea.<ref name="<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+C9C0><U+B09C><U+D574><U+B9CC> 200<U+C5B5> 3<U+B144> <U+B9E4><U+CD9C> 700<U+C5B5> <U+D6CC><U+CA4D>"/> In September 2010, Japanese business magazine ''Nikkei Business'' suggested the group's international expansion and success was the musical equivalent to [[Samsung]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2010/10/02/2010100200238.html|title=Girls' Generation Make Cover of Nikkei Business|date=October 2, 2010|accessdate=November 26, 2012|publisher=english.chosun.com}}</ref> The Institute for Industrial Policy Studies also named the group as one of South Korea's super brands.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newswire.co.kr/newsRead.php?no=587227|title=<U+C0B0><U+C5C5><U+C815><U+CC45><U+C5F0><U+AD6C><U+C6D0>, <U+B300><U+D55C><U+BBFC><U+AD6D> <U+BE0C><U+B79C><U+B4DC> <U+D30C><U+C6CC> 1<U+C704><U+C218><U+D37C><U+BE0C><U+B79C><U+B4DC> <U+C120><U+C815>|year=2011|accessdate=October 31, 2013|publisher=newswire.co.kr|language=Korean}}</ref>

Their popularity in their native Korea has led the group to be named among the most powerful and influential people in the country. The Sisa Journal named the group as the most influential entertainers for the years 2011 and 2012, making them the first female idol group in history to make the list.{{citation needed|date=November 2013}} [[BBC]]'s ''[[Asia Today]]'' placed the group at forty-four on the 50 Korean Power Leaders list in 2011, being the only idol group and entertainers on the list.<ref name="<U+C544><U+C2DC><U+C544><U+D22C><U+B370><U+C774> <U+C120><U+C815>...<U+D55C><U+AD6D><U+C758> <U+D30C><U+C6CC><U+B9AC><U+B354> 50<U+C778>"/> ''[[Forbes]]'' also revealed the group were most powerful entertainers in South Korea for the year of 2011.<ref name="forbes11"/>

In five years the group has earned several major Korean music awards to their name, including five Daesang awards. They won the Disk Daesang for ''[[Oh! (Girls' Generation album)|Oh!]]'' in 2010 at the [[Golden Disk Awards]]. They won the Digital Daesang in 2009 at the same show for "[[Gee (Girls' Generation song)|Gee]]".<ref name="<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+C11C><U+C6B8><U+AC00><U+C694><U+B300><U+C0C1> '<U+B300><U+C0C1>'... 4<U+AD00><U+C655> '<U+C601><U+C608>'"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20101209n29562|date=December 9, 2010|accessdate=November 25, 2012|publisher=news.nate.com|author=<U+C77C><U+AC04><U+C2A4><U+D3EC><U+CE20>|language=Korean|title=[<U+ACE8><U+B4E0>] <U+2018><U+B300><U+C0C1><U+2019> <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, "<U+C544><U+C800><U+C528> <U+D32C> <U+C2E4><U+B9DD> <U+C548><U+C2DC><U+D0AC> <U+AC83>"}}</ref> They won the latter award again in 2011 for "[[The Boys (Girls' Generation song)|The Boys]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://isplus.live.joinsmsn.com/news/article/article.asp?total_id=7125308|title=<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> "<U+D55C> <U+ACE1><U+C774> <U+C544><U+B2CC> <U+C568><U+BC94> <U+C804><U+CCB4> <U+C0AC><U+B791><U+D574><U+C918> <U+AC10><U+C0AC>"|publisher=Sports Daily|language=Korean|date=January 12, 2012|accessdate=November 25, 2012}}</ref> They are among the best-selling artists in South Korea, with over 30 million digital singles and 4.4 million albums sold in less than five years of their debut.<ref name="McCurry">{{cite news|last=McCurry|first=Justin|title=After Psy's Gangnam Style, here come Korea pop princesses Girls' Generation|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/2012/nov/17/girls-generation-psy-gangnam-k-pop|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=November 17, 2012|location=London|date=November 17, 2012}}</ref> Their 2011 album, ''[[The Boys (Girls' Generation album)|The Boys]]'' set a record as the best selling, non-repackaged album in the [[Gaon Chart]]'s history.{{citation needed|date=November 2013}} And they sold over 100,000 copies for each of their six Korean releases, making them the first female group in the South Korean music industry to do so in over six years. The group's success is not limited to South Korea, their debut Japanese album ''[[Girls' Generation (2011 album)|Girls' Generation]]'' is certified 'Million' by the RIAJ, denoting a million copies sold, and is the highest selling album by a Korean group in Oricon history.<ref>[http://www.riaj.or.jp/data/others/gold/201205.html GIRLS' GENERATION have been certified million selling albums by RIAJ]</ref>

==Endorsements==
{{Main|List of Girls' Generation endorsements}}
During their early career, Girls' Generation were endorsers for several brands such as Elite Uniform,<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://joynews.inews24.com/php/news_view.php?g_serial=371708&g_menu=700100 <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>-2PM, <U+C5D8><U+B9AC><U+D2B8><U+D559><U+C0DD><U+BCF5> <U+AD11><U+ACE0> <U+CD2C><U+C601> ('SNSD <U+2013> 2PM At Elite Uniform Photo-Shoot')]</ref> Nexon Bubble Fighter,<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://www.thegamenews.com/gamenews_news/3058/page/113 <U+2018><U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>' 12<U+C6D4><U+BD80><U+D130> <U+BC84><U+BE14><U+D30C><U+C774><U+D130> <U+BAA8><U+B378><U+B85C> <U+B6F4><U+B2E4>]</ref> Samsung and [[LG]].<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://haptic.anycall.com/116 '<U+B2F9><U+C2E0><U+C758> <U+AC10><U+C131><U+ACFC> <U+AD50><U+AC10><U+D558><U+B294> HAPTIC People :: <U+D585><U+D2F1><U+D3F0>, <U+D585><U+D2F1><U+BB38><U+D654><U+B85C> <U+C9C4><U+D654><U+D558><U+B098>?']</ref> The group became the model of an Italian sports brand, [[Ellesse]].<ref>{{cite news|title=<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> <U+C774><U+D0DC><U+B9AC> <U+C2A4><U+D3EC><U+CE20> <U+BE0C><U+B79C><U+B4DC> <U+C5D8><U+B808><U+C384> <U+BAA8><U+B378> <U+BC1C><U+D0C1>|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=200804280949351002|accessdate=December 25, 2012|newspaper=Newsen|date=April 28, 2008}}</ref>

Since 2008 they have been exclusive models for the Goobne Chicken<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://www.sportsseoul.com/news2/life/social/2008/1222/20081222101050100000000_6385307352.html <U+D788><U+D2B8><U+C0C1><U+D488><U+D2B9><U+C9D1>] <U+B9DB><U+C788><U+B294> <U+C0DD><U+AC01> '<U+AD7D><U+B124><U+CE58><U+D0A8>']</ref> and have filmed several commercials for the brand, recorded jingles for advertising purposes, and modeled for promotional Goobne calendars. Goobne Chicken has since become a strong contender in the chicken industry and attribute their success to the group.<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://thestar.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2010/06/23/2010062301733.html <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, '<U+B0B4> <U+C190><U+C744> <U+C804><U+D654><U+AE30><U+B85C> <U+C774><U+B044><U+B294> <U+C720><U+D639><U+C758> <U+CE58><U+D0A8><U+BAA8><U+B378>' 1<U+C704>! (SNSD, 1st Place for 'Tempting Chicken Model Guiding my Hand to the Telephone'!)]</ref>

[[File:<U+B274><U+CD08><U+CF5C><U+B9BF><U+D3F0> <U+C1FC><U+CF00><U+C774><U+C2A4> (3).jpg|thumb|Girls' Generation performs their single "Chocolate Love" at an LG event. The song is a promotional song for LG's Chocolate phone.]]
Several members are solo advertising models such as Seohyun, who models for [[Clean and Clear]] and [[The Face Shop]],<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201002030833341001 '<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> <U+C11C><U+D604>-f(x) <U+D06C><U+B9AC><U+C2A4><U+D0C8>, <U+D654><U+C7A5><U+D488> <U+C804><U+C18D><U+BAA8><U+B378> <U+B3D9><U+BC18><U+BC1C><U+D0C1>']</ref> Taeyeon who models for A-Solution, a cosmetics brand,<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://kr.news.yahoo.com/Biotherm]<br />{{ko icon}} [http://www.biotherm.co.kr/eventcouple/second/notice_detail.jsp?couple_seq=169&notice_seq=4 <U+BE44><U+C624><U+D15C><U+ACFC> <U+D568><U+AED8><U+D558><U+B294> <U+CEE4><U+D50C> UV <U+CCB4><U+D5D8><U+B2E8> <U+BAA8><U+C9D1>]</ref> Yuri who models for [[Mamonde]], Yoona who models for [[S-Oil]],<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://economy.hankooki.com/lpage/industry/201006/e2010062716132947430.htm <U+B9C8><U+CF00><U+D305><U+C73C><U+B85C> <U+C138><U+C0C1><U+C744> <U+BC14><U+AFBC><U+B2E4>] S-OIL]</ref> [[Eider (brand)|EIDER]], FreshLook Illuminate,{{citation needed|date=November 2013}} [[Innisfree (cosmetics brand)|Innisfree]] and Clean and Clear, Jessica for [[Hyundai]] & Banila Co<ref>[http://www.allkpop.com/2012/09/girls-generations-jessica-models-for-cosmetics-brand-banila-co Girls<U+2019> Generation<U+2019>s Jessica models for cosmetics brand <U+2018>banila co.<U+2019>]</ref> and Sooyoung for Llang. Alongside [[Super Junior]], they are also exclusive models to the partly SM Entertainment-owned retail brand SPAO.<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://thestar.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2009/11/25/2009112500720.html <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+C288><U+D37C><U+C8FC><U+B2C8><U+C5B4> '<U+C2A4><U+D30C><U+C624>' <U+B9E4><U+C7A5> <U+C624><U+D508> <U+CEF7><U+D305><U+C2DD> <U+CC38><U+C5EC> ('Girls' Generation and Super Junior, Opening Of SPAO Store')]</ref> Yuri, Sooyoung and Tiffany models for [[Biotherm]].<ref name=allkpop>{{cite news|first=hearfacee|title=SNSD<U+2019>s Yuri, Sooyoung and Tiffany for Biotherm|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2010/03/snsds-yuri-sooyoung-and-tiffany-for-biotherm|accessdate=December 24, 2012|date=March 24, 2012}}</ref>  They endorsed clothing brands, online games,<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://www.gamemeca.com/news/news_view.html?seq=28&ymd=20080801&page=1&point_ck=&search_ym=&search_text= <U+B9C8><U+BE44><U+B178><U+AE30>, <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300><U+AC00> <U+BD80><U+B978> <U+C8FC><U+C81C><U+ACE1> Mabinogi(It's Fantastic!) <U+ACF5><U+AC1C>]</ref> food industries,<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://www.thetimes.kr/news/article.html?no=4913 <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+C0BC><U+C591><U+B77C><U+BA74> CF<U+BAA8><U+B378> <U+BC1C><U+D0C1>! <U+201C><U+C6B0><U+B9B0> <U+C0BC><U+C591><U+B77C><U+BA74> <U+CE5C><U+AD6C><U+201D> (' SNSD Chosen as CF Models of SamYang Ramyun! "We are SamYang Ramyun Friends"')]</ref> events, electronics, cosmetics, and even products reserved for the top celebrities to endorse such as petroleum and [[credit cards]]. The group was one of the most sought-out endorsers in 2009<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://www.newswire.co.kr/newsRead.php?no=429774 '2009 <U+ACE0><U+AC1D><U+AC10><U+B3D9> <U+BC29><U+C1A1><U+AD11><U+ACE0>] <U+C2E0><U+D55C><U+CE74><U+B4DC>...<U+C0C1><U+D07C><U+BC1C><U+B784> <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> '<U+AE0D><U+C815><U+C758> <U+D798>'<U+C744> <U+C0DD><U+AC01><U+D558><U+AC8C> <U+D558><U+B2E4>']</ref> and by mid-2009 the group members were models for over 10 brands and were chosen as one of South Korea's most sought after advertisers in a survey conducted by Brand Consulting Research Institute.<ref name="bntnews.hankyung.com"/>

The group continued to be active in advertising in 2010, endorsing brands and products including the [[Nintendo DSi]]<ref>{{ko icon}}[http://www.todaykorea.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=105176 <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> <U+2018><U+B2CC><U+D150><U+B3C4> DS Crimson/Black' <U+BAA8><U+B378> <U+BC1C><U+D0C1>! ('SNSD Chosen as Models for Nintendo DSi!')]</ref> and [[Domino's Pizza]].<ref>{{ko icon}}[http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?sec=eco99&idxno=2010062810391753300 <U+B3C4><U+BBF8><U+B178><U+D53C><U+C790>, <U+C0C8> CF <U+BAA8><U+B378><U+B85C> '<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>' <U+C120><U+C815> ('SNSD Selected as New CF Model for Domino Pizza')]</ref> Also, a [[Caribbean Bay]] commercial featured Yuri, Yoona and Seohyun along with [[2PM]] members [[Nichkhun]], [[Taecyeon]] and [[Chansung]]. In late 2010, a gift certificate company began releasing gift certificates each worth 10,000 [[South Korean won|won]] which featured Girls' Generation images on the cards, making them the first celebrities to be featured as such.<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://star.mt.co.kr/view/stview.php?no=2010092014183109937&type=1&outlink=1 <U+97D3><U+C5F0><U+C608><U+C778> <U+CD5C><U+CD08> '<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> <U+C0C1><U+D488><U+AD8C>' <U+B098><U+C628><U+B2E4> (First celebrities to have their own gift certificate <U+201C>Girls' Generation gift cards<U+201D>)]</ref> The Korean web portal [[Daum Communications|Daum]] also began using the group as models while remodeling certain services and search engines in early October 2010, and released Girls' Generation [[Computer wallpaper|desktop wallpapers]] and [[screensaver]]s for promotion.<ref>{{ko icon}} [http://isplus.joins.com/article/article.html?aid=1519150 <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+C2A4><U+D06C><U+B9B0><U+C138><U+C774><U+BC84><U+B85C> <U+C778><U+AE30><U+BAB0><U+C774> (Sonyeo Sidae Screen Savers Increase In Popularity)]</ref> A survey conducted in December 2010 saw 409 out of 741 marketing employees choosing Girls' Generation as the model with the most influence over consumers.<ref name="acrofan.com"/>

In 2011, [[Intel]] Asia announced that the group would become official advertising models for the company.<ref>{{ko icon}}[http://news.nate.com/view/20110109n02981 <U+C778><U+D154>, <U+C544><U+C2DC><U+C544> <U+AD11><U+ACE0> <U+BAA8><U+B378> `<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>` <U+BC1C><U+D0C1> (SNSD selected to be advertisement models for Intel Asia)]</ref> In March 2011, the group started endorsing the Vita500 brand of energy drinks as part of Vita500's 10th anniversary<ref>{{ko icon}}{{Cite news|title=''<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> <U+BE44><U+D0C0>500' <U+B9C8><U+C2DC><U+C790>... <U+D574><U+C678><U+C11C><U+B3C4> <U+D6C4><U+B048>''|newspaper=Nate News|author=<U+C774><U+B3D9><U+D604>|agency=Nate|language=Korean}}</ref> and exclusive Vita500 posters of Tiffany, Yuri and Yoona were released.<ref>{{Cite news|title=<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300> <U+C724><U+C544> '<U+CCAD><U+C21C><U+AC00><U+B828> <U+C885><U+ACB0><U+C790>?' <U+BE44><U+D0C0>500 <U+AC1C><U+C778> <U+D3EC><U+C2A4><U+D130> <U+ACF5><U+AC1C> '<U+D669><U+D640>'|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20110310n18575|accessdate=June 23, 2011|newspaper=Nate News|author=<U+AE40><U+B3C4><U+ACBD>|agency=Nate|language=Korean}}</ref> Members Yuri, Sunny, Jessica, Tiffany, Sooyoung, and Hyoyeon were models for [[Christian Dior S.A.|Christian Dior]]. Yoona, Seohyun, and Taeyeon were not models, due to other cosmetic contracts. Woongjin Coway selected the group as their exclusive models to endorse their water purifiers. Their contract began on March 1, 2011, and lasted throughout the year, with TV advertisements beginning in mid-March.

In Japan, the group endorsed the [[throat lozenge]] brand ''E-ma Nodoame''.<ref>{{cite news |language =ja | url =http://www.hotexpress.co.jp/news/110222_girlsgeneration/ | title =<U+5C11><U+5973><U+6642><U+4EE3> <U+65B0>CM<U+767A><U+8868><U+4F1A><U+3067><U+300C><U+6163><U+308C><U+3066><U+304D><U+3066><U+4ECA><U+306F><U+697D><U+3057><U+3081><U+308B><U+69D8><U+306B><U+300D> | publisher=hot express | date =February 22, 2011 | accessdate =February 22, 2011}}</ref> They endorsed [[Lipton]] tea with their songs "Let It Rain" and "Mr. Taxi" used as background music.<ref>{{jp icon}}{{cite web|title=<U+3042><U+306A><U+305F><U+306E><U+597D><U+307F><U+306F><U+30AD><U+30E5><U+30FC><U+30C8>?<U+3000><U+30AF><U+30FC><U+30EB>?<U+3000><U+5C11><U+5973><U+6642><U+4EE3><U+304C><U+3008><U+30EA><U+30D7><U+30C8><U+30F3><U+3009><U+65B0>CM<U+306B><U+767B><U+5834>|url=http://tower.jp/article/news/78447|publisher=Tower Records|accessdate=June 23, 2011|language=Japanese}}</ref> In July 2011, along with labelmate [[TVXQ]], they started endorsing [[7-Eleven]] Japan products featuring the Japanese version of the song "[[Hoot (song)|Hoot]]" in commercials.<ref>{{jp icon}}{{cite web|title=7-Eleven Japan Product Homepage|url=http://www.sej.co.jp/products/kpop011107.html|publisher=7-Eleven Japan|accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> The group were appointed models for J.ESTINA in October 2011. Seohyun was appointed as [[UNICEF]] envoy during the same month. This is a notable feat, as only those who have a respectable reputation are appointed as [[List of UNICEF Goodwill Ambassadors|Goodwill]] representatives. Two months later, on December 15, JCE chose Girls<U+2019> Generation as the models for their representative bundled game brand, <U+201C>Freestyle Sports<U+201D>, for that winter.

[[File:SNSD Cooky Phone.jpg|thumb|left|The group has made many ads for the Korean market, including this one for the LG Cookie.]]
The group were selected as honorary ambassadors for Korea's "Visit Korea 2010 <U+2013> 2012" campaign, headed by South Korea's First Lady, [[Kim Yoon-ok]]. The campaign was an effort by the Korean government to attract at least 10 million foreign visitors to the country by the end of 2012, with the group spearheading the initiative due to their emerging worldwide popularity at the time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.visitkoreayear.com/english/community/community_01_01_01_view.asp?bidx=205&st&sech&page=1|title=Girls` Generation Appointed as Honorary Ambassadors for the Visit Korea Year Campaign|date=August 8, 2011|accessdate=July 12, 2012|publisher=english.visitkoreayear.com}}</ref> [[LG Electronics]] Korea announced on January 16, 2012, that Girls' Generation were chosen to be the new models for their Cinema 3D TV brand.

On March 5, representatives of [[Gangnam-gu]] in Seoul released a statement stating that the Girls' Generation would be the honorary ambassadors for the city of starting on March 7, 2012. In the same month, [[Lotte (conglomerate)|Lotte]] announced that the group was chosen to be the new models for [[Lotte Department Store]]. They were also chosen to be models for ACE Bed. On April 14, Girls<U+2019> Generation were appointed as new ambassadors for the association Korea<U+2019>s Retinitis Pigmentosa Society, a society dedicated to help find a for cure blindness. They had also been chosen as the newest endorsers for [[Korea Yakult]]. In May 2012, Tiffany and Jessica were chosen as model for [[Chanel]] cosmetics pop-up store.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.allkpop.com/2012/05/girls-generations-jessica-and-tiffany-model-chanel-for-vogue-girl | title=Girls<U+2019> Generation<U+2019>s Jessica and Tiffany model Chanel for <U+2018>Vogue Girl<U+2019> | publisher=allkpop | date=May 20, 2012}}</ref>

In September 2012, Tiffany started endorsing the fashion brand [[Bean Pole International|Bean Pole]].{{citation needed|date=December 2013}} Girls Generation became the endorser of GiRL de Provence perfume from [[10 Corso Como]].{{citation needed|date=November 2013}} Electronics brand, [[Casio]], appointed the group as the endorsers for the company's [[watch]] brand, [[Baby-G]]. The contract is scheduled to last over a year, and Casio hopes to have a fifty percent increase in sales for 2013, compared to that of 2011.{{citation needed|date=November 2013}} [[G-Star Raw]] Japan has chosen Girls' Generation, as the muse for their 2013 Spring/Summer season.{{citation needed|date=November 2013}} In January 2013, Jessica, along with her sister [[Krystal (singer)|Krystal]], became the new faces of jewelry brand, Stonehenge.<ref>{{cite news|title=SNSD<U+2019>s Jessica-f(x)<U+2019>s Krystal Siblings Model for Stonehenge|url=http://global.mnet.com/news/newsdetail.m?searchNewsVO.news_id=201301071425_25750|accessdate=January 12, 2013|newspaper=MNET|date=January 7, 2013}}</ref>

In 2012 list of stars with the most CFs Girls<U+2019> Generation as an entire group are in 1st place, combined, the girls are models to a total of 21 different brands including chicken, perfume, jewelry, handbags, TVs, beds, and department stores while Jessica & Yoona were tied for 2nd place for Individually CFs by participating in 13 different CFs, Tiffany was in the 3rd place with 12 CFs and Seohyun, Sooyoung and Yuri in 4th place with 11 CFs.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.allkpop.com/2013/02/suzy-surpasses-girls-generation-to-become-the-1-cf-queen | title=Suzy surpasses Girls<U+2019> Generation to become the #1 CF Queen | publisher=allkpop | date=February 7, 2013}}</ref>

Girls' Generation pair up with 'Hair Couture' for hair fashion. Hair Couture produces and distributes fashion wigs to countries all over the world, including the United States. They will start distributing these products in Korea in June, and they will also be released in China, Taiwan, and Thailand.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.allkpop.com/2013/03/girls-generation-pair-up-with-hair-couture-for-hair-fashion | title=Girls<U+2019> Generation pair up with Hair Couture for hair fashion | publisher=allkpop | date=March 28, 2013 | accessdate=March 28, 2013}}</ref>

==Philanthropy==
Girls' Generation held a donation campaign on February 4, 2010 with music site ''Lunchbox'' for the "Music Dream" campaign. Three percent of the purchase price was donated to the Korean [[Make-A-Wish Foundation]]. A portion of the revenue from their Japanese single "[[Mr. Taxi / Run Devil Run]]", released April 27, 2011, was donated to Japan's [[Red Cross]] in order to provide assistance for the victims of the [[2011 T<U+014D>hoku earthquake and tsunami]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=[<U+C560><U+D504><U+D130><U+C2A4><U+D1A0><U+B9AC>]<U+C77C><U+BCF8> <U+B300><U+C9C0><U+C9C4><U+C73C><U+B85C> <U+D65C><U+B3D9> <U+C5F0><U+AE30><U+B41C> <U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+BB50><U+D558><U+B098> <U+BD24><U+B354><U+B2C8>|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20110414n13640|accessdate=June 16, 2011|newspaper=Nate|author=<U+C774><U+C815><U+D601>|agency=Nate|language=Korean}}</ref> The group also donated signed handbags that were auctioned off.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ajw.asahi.com/article/0311disaster/recovery/AJ201203210015|date=March 21, 2011|accessdate=November 25, 2012|publisher=ajw.ashai.com|author=KAZUYA OMURO|title=K-pop stars donate memorabilia to help quake victims}}</ref>

On August 9, 2011, they, and their label mates [[f(x) (band)|f(x)]] and [[SHINee]], took part in an effort to help African children. The groups were joined by the [[United Nation]]'s Secretary-General, [[Ban Ki-moon]], in the "Help African Children" project co-organized by the [[Republic of Korea National Red Cross|Korean Red Cross Society]] and the Korean [[UNICEF]] committee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2011/08/10/snsd-and-other-celebrities-join-un-secretarygeneral-ban-ki-moons-help-african-children/|title=SNSD and Other Celebrities Join UN Secretary-General Ban Ki Moon<U+2019>s "Help African Children"|publisher=soompi.com|author=hazelnutthursdays|date=August 10, 2011|accessdate=August 27, 2012}}</ref>

The group, along with [[Super Junior]], appeared on a special episode of [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]'s ''Love Request'' broadcast on September 17, 2011, where they invited an 11-year-old Cambodian girl with a heart problem and a blind boy to fly to Korea to receive treatment, as well as a young girl from Korea who had lived in a hotel with her widowed mother her entire life. The two groups also participated in a [[Blood donation|blood drive]] at the KBS Hall. During the 85 minute broadcast, over 32 million won (US$29,000) was raised.<ref>[http://www.soshified.com/2011/09/girls-generation-appears-on-love-request Girls<U+2019> Generation Appears on <U+2018>Love Request<U+2019>]</ref>
In the same month, Woongjin Coway held a <U+201C>Beautiful Auction<U+201D> event at [[Times Square (Seoul)|Times Square]] in [[Yeongdeungpo]] with Girls' Generation on September 27, 2011 to help women who are [[Domestic violence|neglected]]. They auctioned their outfits and accessories which they wore in their CFs to raise funds for the charity.<ref>[http://www.wonderfulgeneration.net/2011/10/snsd-at-special-charity-auction-event.html SNSD at Woongjin Coway's Special Charity Auction Event]</ref>

In April 2012, the Korean Association Against Blindness announced that the group would be the official face of their movement.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joinsmsn.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2951234|title=Girls<U+2019> Generation to be eye candy for anti-blindness movement|date=April 9, 2012|accessdate=July 8, 2012|publisher=koreajoongangdaily.joinsmsn.com}}</ref> On August 17, 2012, it was revealed that Girls<U+2019> Generation's outfits are sent to philanthropic organizations and are put up for auction. The money is then donated to a good cause.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20120816n14244&mid=e0403&cid=374678|language=korean|title=[<U+AC78>,<U+C637>] "<U+CEF4><U+D50C><U+B809><U+C2A4>, <U+C5B4><U+B5BB><U+AC8C> <U+AC00><U+B9B4><U+AE4C>?"<U+2026><U+BB34><U+B300><U+C758><U+C0C1> <U+AD81><U+AE08><U+C99D> '9'|publisher=news.nate.com|date=August 16, 2012|accessdate=August 17, 2012}}</ref> That same week, the Korean Post announced that profits of the group's official stamps would be donated to Merry Year, a charity.<ref name="Stewart Ho 1"/> Girls<U+2019> Generation donated eight tons of rice to help those who are in need. It was revealed that the rice donations made by the group on December 5, 2012, was able to help 66,400 people in need.<ref>{{cite news|title=(Korean)"<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300>, <U+AC15><U+B0A8><U+AD6C><U+C5D0> <U+C0AC><U+B791><U+C758> <U+C300> <U+C804><U+B2EC>|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=102&oid=003&aid=0004864051|accessdate=January 11, 2013|newspaper=Naver|date=December 5, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=(Korean)<U+C18C><U+B140><U+C2DC><U+B300><U+AC00> <U+AE30><U+BD80><U+D55C> <U+C300> 8t <U+C54C><U+ACE0> <U+BCF4><U+B2C8><U+2026><U+D32C><U+B4E4><U+C774> <U+C2ED><U+C2DC><U+C77C><U+BC18> <U+BAA8><U+C544>|url=http://article.joinsmsn.com/news/article/article.asp?total_id=10082026|accessdate=January 11, 2013|newspaper=joinmsn|date=December 5, 2012}}</ref> On December 17, 2012, Tiffany was appointed as the honorary ambassador for Global Hope, which is listed as a non-profit corporation by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade, and aims to build a hopeful community by digging up talents and encouraging leadership across six countries.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kim|first=Erika|title=SNSD<U+2032>s Tiffany Appointed Honorary Ambassador for Global Hope|url=http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=25148|accessdate=December 29, 2012|newspaper=enewsWorld|date=December 28, 2012|agency=CJ E&M enewsWorld}}</ref>

Girls' Generation donated group merchandise and several personal items to the 'Star Donation Event', where their items were auctioned off for charity. Over three million South Korean Won (over $3,000 USD) was raised and donated to the [[Holt International Children's Services|Holt Children's Center]].<ref>[http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/09/teen-tops-rickys-bracelet-is-the-highest-bid-item-at-star-donation-which-included-goods-from-girls-generation-secret-shinee-and-sistar Goods from Girls' Generation, SECRET, SHINee, and SISTAR]</ref>

On November 19, 2013 member [[Seohyun]] donated 100 million won scholarship to [[Dongguk University]]. She attended the scholarship fund ceremony held at Lotus Hall inside the main building of Dongguk University and was recognized for her donation by the university chancellor Kim Hee Ok.<ref>[Girls' Generation's Seohyun donates 100 million won scholarship to Dongguk University]</ref>

